{"type":"message","id":"f57e8b54","parentId":"64b48b1f","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:06:21.367Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_3y7xob4f3zjj_1","toolName":"sessions_list","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"count\": 20,\n  \"sessions\": [\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"unknown\",\n      \"label\": \"Cron: Agent Status to Lead\",\n      \"displayName\": \"Cron: Agent Status to Lead\",\n      \"updatedAt\": 1776171973947,\n      \"sessionId\": \"24ebc881-f0ee-4764-951f-beb479672401\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 21825,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"running\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1776171973499,\n      \"systemSent\": true,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/24ebc881-f0ee-4764-951f-beb479672401.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": [\n        {\n          \"role\": \"user\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"[cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e Agent Status to Lead] You are Orbis. Check sessions_list and compile a brief status of all ACTIVE master-orchestrator sessions (excluding this cron session).\\n\\nFor each active session, report:\\n- Session key (shortened)\\n- Status (running/done)\\n- What it's doing (from context)\\n- How long it's been running\\n\\nSend the report to Lead directly via sessions_send to sessionKey: agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134\\n\\nFormat:\\n🌐 Orbis — Agent Status | {HH:MM} UTC {DD MMM}\\n\\nActive sessions: N\\n• [session name]: [status] — [task/description] — [duration]\\n\\nIf only this cron session is active (no other sessions), send HEARTBEAT_OK only.\\nIf there are no sessions at all, stay SILENT.\\nCurrent time: Tuesday, April 14th, 2026 - 1:05 PM (UTC) / 2026-04-14 13:05 UTC\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"timestamp\": 1776171973498,\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"93b49a9e\",\n            \"seq\": 1\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"Let me check the sessions list to see what active master-orchestrator sessions are running.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n              \"id\": \"call_function_3y7xob4f3zjj_1\",\n              \"name\": \"sessions_list\",\n              \"arguments\": {\n                \"kinds\": [\n                  \"agent\"\n                ],\n                \"limit\": 20,\n                \"messageLimit\": 3\n              }\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 325,\n            \"output\": 69,\n            \"totalTokens\": 13449,\n            \"cacheRead\": 0,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 13055,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1776171973658,\n          \"responseId\": \"062d6ec63dea3c43bbcc8220f82c145c\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"64b48b1f\",\n            \"seq\": 2\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"webchat\",\n      \"label\": \"Cron: 5p Progress Report - DTLX\",\n      \"displayName\": \"webchat:g-agent-master-orchestrator-cron-6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31\",\n      \"deliveryContext\": {\n        \"channel\": \"webchat\"\n      },\n      \"updatedAt\": 1776171848941,\n      \"sessionId\": \"c12d4d65-c174-403b-9368-ed39dd7f0949\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 27925,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"running\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1776152701090,\n      \"systemSent\": true,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"lastChannel\": \"webchat\",\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/c12d4d65-c174-403b-9368-ed39dd7f0949.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": [\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"Let me compare the current sessions_list (which returned 0 sessions) against the saved state. \\n\\nCurrent state shows several sessions, but sessions_list shows 0 sessions. This is unusual - the sessions might be running under different visibility. Let me check more carefully.\\n\\nActually, looking at the sessions_list result - it returned `{\\\"count\\\": 0, \\\"sessions\\\": []}`. But the heartbeat-state shows many sessions. This discrepancy could mean:\\n\\n1. The sessions are in a different state/visibility\\n2. The sessions_list API has different filters\\n3. There may be a real change in session state\\n\\nBut wait - the current time is 13:04 UTC and the lastHeartbeat was at 12:46 UTC. That's 18 minutes ago. \\n\\nThe cron job ID `6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31` matches between the stored state and this execution, which is a good sign. The heartbeat is only 18 minutes old, so this cron job is running as expected. I need to call sessions_list without filters to get the full picture.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n              \"id\": \"call_function_vx89k3trsa8b_1\",\n              \"name\": \"sessions_list\",\n              \"arguments\": {}\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 969,\n            \"output\": 246,\n            \"totalTokens\": 15723,\n            \"cacheRead\": 14264,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 244,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1776171875448,\n          \"responseId\": \"062d6e64251bab658270e42941c3c6d9\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"bac55f0a\",\n            \"seq\": 7\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"Now I need to compare the current state against the last known state in heartbeat-state.json. Let me analyze the key differences:\\n\\n**Last known state (heartbeat-state.json):**\\n- main session: done (endedAt: 2026-04-14T12:29:00Z)\\n- QLHV Ecosystem Group: running\\n- DTLX Ecosystem Group: done (endedAt: 2026-04-14T10:55:00Z)\\n- Lead Direct: done\\n- Cron sessions: various statuses\\n\\n**Current state (sessions_list at 13:04 UTC):**\\n\\nNew/different items compared to last state:\\n\\n\\nThe main session is still marked done in both snapshots, and the QLHV Ecosystem Group transitioned to done status. The cron sessions show continued activity with the agent status check, 11:53 UTC report, and Telegram retry all persisting. I should continue scanning through the rest of the session list to identify any other changes.\\n\\nLooking at the updated timestamps more carefully—the main session ended at 12:29 UTC and the new one just started at 13:04 UTC, which means they are distinct sessions rather than the same one continuing. The main session key changed from one UUID to another, confirming this is a fresh instance rather than a carryover.\\n\\nNow I'm comparing the session keys from the heartbeat-state file against the current active sessions to see which ones are new versus persistent. Most of the cron sessions and the QLHV group are still running, but there are a few entries in the heartbeat that don't appear in the current active list—those must have completed or been cleaned up.\\n\\nThe main difference I'm noticing is that a new main session has started at 13:04, whereas the previous one ended around 12:29. So the key change here is just that fresh main session spinning up.\\n\\nNow I need to figure out whether this DTLX report should go to group -5163901258 or -5168104492—the task specifies -5163901258, but that's the QLHV group, not the DTLX group, so there might be some confusion about which ecosystem this report is actually meant for.\\n\\nLooking at the active sessions for the DTLX ecosystem specifically, I see there are 2 cron jobs and 1 completed session running. Since the last heartbeat was at 12:46 and the current time is 13:04, I'm checking if anything significant has changed in those sessions.\\n\\nThe main heartbeat session ended and was replaced by a new one, which represents a state transition but isn't necessarily an ecosystem change. The cron sessions are still running as expected, and the pipeline health looks stable with the MCP servers operational. I don't see any active failures, blockers, or new sessions that would warrant an immediate report—the system appears to be in a steady state despite the session replacement.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"No changes detected. Stable since 11:53 UTC. Silent exit.\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 12307,\n            \"output\": 598,\n            \"totalTokens\": 28523,\n            \"cacheRead\": 14433,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 1185,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1776171884096,\n          \"responseId\": \"062d6e6c276554dd9d0ab62e611efa6c\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"d16538e4\",\n            \"seq\": 9\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"webchat\",\n      \"origin\": {\n        \"provider\": \"heartbeat\"\n      },\n      \"label\": \"Cron: 5p Progress Report\",\n      \"displayName\": \"webchat:g-agent-master-orchestrator-cron-ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7\",\n      \"deliveryContext\": {\n        \"channel\": \"webchat\"\n      },\n      \"updatedAt\": 1776171705835,\n      \"sessionId\": \"2181599d-2279-4f64-b28c-e4350c462cf6\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 43555,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"running\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1776154374281,\n      \"systemSent\": true,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"lastChannel\": \"webchat\",\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/2181599d-2279-4f64-b28c-e4350c462cf6.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": [\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"Now I need to compare the current sessions against the last known state. Let me analyze the current sessions list vs the heartbeat-state.json.\\n\\n**Last heartbeat state (12:46 UTC):**\\n1. `cron:ed2d0b5d` (QLHV 5p): running, updatedAt 1776170845566\\n2. `cron:6f3323ef` (DTLX 5p): running, updatedAt 1776170596777\\n3. `telegram:group:-5163901258` (QLHV): running\\n4. `telegram:group:-5168104492` (DTLX): done\\n\\n\\n5. `telegram:direct:6053576134` (Lead): done\\n6. `main` (heartbeat): done\\n7. `cron:e7885813` (Agent Status): running, lastSeen 12:34\\n8. `cron:b653a6c0` (zombie): running, lastSeen 11:53\\n9. `cron:ac986a8d`: done\\n\\n**Current state (13:01 UTC):**\\nThe 5p QLHV cron has advanced normally, and the DTLX cron appears to be progressing as expected.\\n\\nLooking at the remaining sessions, the Agent Status cron just fired successfully at 13:01 UTC, and the zombie cron is still stale but pre-existing. The DTLX group and Lead direct sessions remain done, and the main heartbeat is stable. Overall, no new failures or blockers—just normal progression across the active crons. Everything checks out.\\n\\nWait, let me double-check the Agent Status cron. It shows updatedAt 1776171294257, which converts to around 13:01 UTC, same timestamp as my current check. That makes sense since this is a 5-minute cron that fires at the start of each minute. So it's been running with normal ticks throughout—no significant state changes to report. Time to update the heartbeat and stay quiet.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"Silent exit. All sessions stable vs last heartbeat (12:46 UTC):\\n\\n- `cron:ed2d0b5d` (QLHV 5p): running ✅ — normal tick\\n- `cron:6f3323ef` (DTLX 5p): running ✅ — normal tick\\n- `cron:e7885813` (Agent Status): running ✅ — alive\\n- `cron:b653a6c0` (zombie): stale, pre-existing ✅\\n- All others: stable ✅\\n\\nNo new failures, deaths, blockers, or session state changes. Pipeline stable.\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 29167,\n            \"output\": 542,\n            \"totalTokens\": 44097,\n            \"cacheRead\": 13944,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 444,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1776171750119,\n          \"responseId\": \"062d6de72230be1bc1c1137110bf2020\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"017267b2\",\n            \"seq\": 5\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:main\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"webchat\",\n      \"origin\": {\n        \"provider\": \"heartbeat\"\n      },\n      \"displayName\": \"webchat:g-agent-master-orchestrator-main\",\n      \"deliveryContext\": {\n        \"channel\": \"webchat\",\n        \"to\": \"heartbeat\"\n      },\n      \"updatedAt\": 1776171612342,\n      \"sessionId\": \"bca9bbb9-d1eb-408d-9e3d-14dd521dcc45\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 67879,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"done\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1776171601577,\n      \"endedAt\": 1776171610264,\n      \"runtimeMs\": 8687,\n      \"systemSent\": true,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"lastChannel\": \"webchat\",\n      \"lastTo\": \"heartbeat\",\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/bca9bbb9-d1eb-408d-9e3d-14dd521dcc45.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": [\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"The Agent Status cron (e7885813) sent its report to me (the main session via webchat). It noted the cron itself is stale because its delivery target (Lead Telegram direct) ended. The cron has a new session ID (169012dd) and is running.\\n\\nThe cron recommends updating the delivery target. Since the Lead's Telegram session is done, the Agent Status cron should target the main session or the group. However, since the cron itself is a separate orchestration mechanism that I didn't set up, and it has a new running session now, I should let it continue and just monitor.\\n\\nThe key issue flagged is: the Agent Status cron keeps retrying to send to Lead's Telegram direct (which is done) and going stale. \\n\\nI'll accept this as operational feedback—it's pointing out the staleness problem but it does have a fresh session running, so the main pipeline is stable with 3 active sessions.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"🟡 **Orbis — Status Acknowledged** | 12:56 UTC 14 Apr\\n\\nAgent Status cron (e7885813) report received via main session. Noted:\\n\\n- **Pipeline: HEALTHY** ✅ — 3 active sessions (2× 5p crons + Agent Status)\\n- **Delivery issue**: Agent Status cron targeting Lead Telegram direct (ended ~12:15 UTC) → stale cycle detected\\n- **Action**: Cron has new session (169012dd) — let it self-resolve on next cycle. If it persists, will kill and respawn targeting main session\\n\\nUpdating state and staying silent. No intervention needed.\\n\\n— Orbis 🌐\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 1797,\n            \"output\": 331,\n            \"totalTokens\": 66295,\n            \"cacheRead\": 63773,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 394,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1776171469925,\n          \"responseId\": \"062d6ccf0b681d6cf20c06a211d2e1dd\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"2be81fd3\",\n            \"seq\": 115\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"role\": \"user\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"System: [2026-04-14 12:31:58 UTC] Silent exit — no changes detected since last report (12:29 UTC). All monitored sessions stable. Pipeline healthy.\\nSystem: [2026-04-14 12:34:09 UTC] Comparing current sessions against `heartbeat-state.json` (lastHeartbeat: 12:23 UTC):\\nSystem: \\nSystem: **Key sessions:**\\nSystem: - `cron:e